Package net.sf.cotelab.util.collections

Interface MultiMap<K,V>

Type Parameters:
K - the type of key to be supported.
V - the type of value to be supported.
All Known Subinterfaces:
BidiMultiMap<K,V>
All Known Implementing Classes:
HashBidiMultiMap, HashMultiMap
public interface MultiMap<K,V>
A map which allows multiple values per key. This interface is similar to Map, but while the entries in an ordinary map have unique keys, the entries in a MultiMap are unique by key-value pair.

The behavior of a MultiMap is undefined if its keys or values are mutable.

All general-purpose MultiMap implementation classes should provide three "standard" constructors:

A void (no arguments) constructor
Create an empty MultiMap
A constructor with a single argument of type Map
Create a new MultiMap with the same key-value mappings as its argument
A constructor with a single argument of type MultiMap
Create a new (MultiMap with the same key-value mappings as its argument

As with the standard Java collections classes, instances of MultiMap are unsynchronized.

Author:
alancote@rochester.rr.com
